<!--  Only use Generic.xaml to style custom controls inside the project.  -->

<!--
    It is impossible to access resources in generic.xaml from code behind. There is nothing similar to Application.Current.Resources[] available.
    Default styles for custom controls MUST be defined in generic.xaml, otherwise automatic style inheritance by an application developer will not work.
    If you want styles to be accessible from code behind, they must be in the AppDictionary.xaml (App.xaml)
    
    http://putridparrot.com/blog/accessing-xaml-resources-in-code/
-->

